

Installation instructions:
===========================================================================================

1. Copy the Makefile closest to your system
   $ cp Makefile.XXX Makefile
2. Adjust Makefile as needed
3. Run the command
   $make

===========================================================================================


Dependencies needed to compile and run the programs:
===========================================================================================

Necessary dependencies:

1. Bash shell environment (http://www.gnu.org/software/bash/). 
   Can use MinGW on windows (http://www.mingw.org/).
2. Fortran and C/C++ compilers. 
   Tested with gfortran (http://gcc.gnu.org/fortran/) and gcc (http://gcc.gnu.org/).
   Also tested with ifort and icc (http://software.intel.com/en-us/intel-compilers)
3. GNU Make (http://www.gnu.org/software/make/).
4. Any implementation of MPI. Tested using OpenMPI (http://www.open-mpi.org/).
5. Petsc compiled with complex data type and optionally HDF5 (http://www.mcs.anl.gov/petsc/).
   Petsc installer can download and install MPI and HDF5 (optional).
6. Slepc compiled on Petsc installation as above (http://www.grycap.upv.es/slepc/).
7. GNU Scientific Library (http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/).

Optional dependencies:

1. Parallel HDF5 libraries (http://www.hdfgroup.org/HDF5/PHDF5/).
2. X window system: 
   Either x-org (http://www.x.org) , Cygwin/X (http://x.cygwin.com/) or 
   something similar like Xming (http://www.straightrunning.com/XmingNotes/)
3. Python for converting PetSc binary to ASCII text (http://www.python.org/).
   Additionally, Numpy (http://www.numpy.org/) may also be installed.

===========================================================================================
